   <concept id="FAR_23_103" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">23.103</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1507e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Agencies shall procure sustainable products and services (as defined in <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="FAR-2.101"
                        xtrc="2.101"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>) to the maximum extent practicable.</p>
               <ol id="d1507e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>  Procuring sustainable products and services is considered practicable, unless the agency cannot acquire products or services—</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e22">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Competitively within a reasonable performance schedule;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e27">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> That meet reasonable performance requirements; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e32">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> At a reasonable price (see <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    href="23.103.dita#FAR_23_103"
                                    base="FAR-23.103"
                                    xtrc="23.103"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">23.103</xref>(a)(2)).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e21">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>  When considering whether the price of a sustainable product is reasonable, agencies should consider whether the product is cost-effective over the life of the product. For ENERGY STAR® or Federal Energy Management Program (FEMP)-designated products, a price is reasonable if it is cost-effective over the life of the product taking energy cost savings into account (<xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section8259&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. 8259b(b)(2)</xref>). Life-cycle cost savings tools for energy-efficient products are available at <xref href="https://www.energystar.gov/buildings/save_energy_commercial_buildings/ways_save/energy_efficient_products"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://www.energystar.gov/​buildings/​save_​energy_​commercial_​buildings/​ways_​save/​energy_​efficient_​products</xref> and <xref href="https://www.nrel.gov/analysis/tech-lcoe.html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://www.nrel.gov/​analysis/​tech-lcoe.html</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e49">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>  When procuring sustainable products and services, agencies shall—</p>
               <ol id="d1507e93" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e55">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Ensure compliance with applicable statutory purchasing program requirements (see <xref href="23.107.dita#FAR_23_107"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.107</xref>); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e60">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Prioritize multi-attribute sustainable products and services (see <xref href="23.104.dita#FAR_23_104"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.104</xref>(c)(2)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1529e70">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>  Regarding products under contract actions for services or construction, the contractor is required to provide products that meet the definition of sustainable products and services at <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>, if the products are—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e82">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Delivered to the Government;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e87">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Furnished by the contractor for use by the Government;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e92">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Incorporated into the construction of a public building or public work; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1527e97">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Acquired by the contractor for use in performing services under a Government contract where the cost of the products is a direct cost to a Government contract (versus costs which are normally applied to a contractor's general and administrative expenses or indirect costs).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
